body_html:
@dsmilkov I built the latest version, however, the problem still exists. There's no error messages, only a warning in chrome console:
/deep/ combinator is deprecated. See https://www.chromestatus.com/features/6750456638341120 for more details..
Btw, I adjusted a bit code in google/protobuf/src/google/protobuf/io/coded_stream.h : 611:

static const int kDefaultTotalBytesLimit = 256 << 20;  // 64MB

in order to load my large tensorflow log file. But I don't think this will cause problem.
I use Chrome 47.0.

body:
@dsmilkov I built the latest version, however, the problem still exists. There's no error messages, only a warning in chrome console: 
`/deep/ combinator is deprecated. See https://www.chromestatus.com/features/6750456638341120 for more details.`.
Btw, I adjusted a bit code in `google/protobuf/src/google/protobuf/io/coded_stream.h : 611`:

```
static const int kDefaultTotalBytesLimit = 256 << 20;  // 64MB
```

in order to load my large tensorflow log file. But I don't think this will cause problem.
I use Chrome 47.0.
